    "messageBody": "<div id=\"ygrps-yiv-20141139\">\n<html><head>\n \n</head> \n\n \n<div><span class=\"ygrps-yiv-20141139306411804-20122000\"><font size=\"2\">Here is an example from one of \nAnt&#39;s super test classes&nbsp;which is also pretty sweet:</font></span></div>\n<div><font size=\"2\"></font>&nbsp;</div>\n<div><font size=\"2\"></font>&nbsp;</div>\n<div><font size=\"2\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; protected void expectBuildException(String \ntaskname, String cause) { <br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; try { \n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; \nexecuteTarget(taskname);<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; } catch \n(org.apache.tools.ant.BuildException ex) { \n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; \nreturn;<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; \n}<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; fail(&quot;Should throw \nBuildException because: &quot; + cause);<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; }</font></div>\n<div><font size=\"2\"></font>&nbsp;</div>\n<div><span class=\"ygrps-yiv-20141139306411804-20122000\"><font size=\"2\"></font></span>&nbsp;</div>\n<div><span class=\"ygrps-yiv-20141139306411804-20122000\"><font size=\"2\">and example test which uses \nit:</font></span></div>\n<div><span class=\"ygrps-yiv-20141139306411804-20122000\"><font size=\"2\"></font></span>&nbsp;</div>\n<div><span class=\"ygrps-yiv-20141139306411804-20122000\"><font size=\"2\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; public void \ntest1() { <br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; \nexpectBuildException(&quot;test1&quot;, &quot;required argument not \nspecified&quot;);<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; }<br></font></span></div>\n<div><font size=\"2\"></font>&nbsp;</div>\n<blockquote><span title=\"qreply\"> <blockquote\n style=\"PADDING-LEFT:5px;MARGIN-LEFT:5px;BORDER-LEFT:#000000 2px solid;\">\n  <div class=\"ygrps-yiv-20141139OutlookMessageHeader\" dir=\"ltr\" align=\"left\"><font face=\"Tahoma\"\n size=\"2\">-----Original Message-----<br><b>From:</b> sachin gupta \n  [mailto:sachin@...]<br><b>Sent:</b> Tuesday, December 19, 2000 5:15 \n  PM<br><b>To:</b> junit@egroups.com<br><b>Subject:</b> RE: [junit] Exception \n  Handling Question<br><br></font></div>\n  <div><span class=\"ygrps-yiv-20141139323270601-20122000\"><font size=\"2\">Thank you for making me more \n  efficient :)&nbsp; There are so many ways&nbsp;we can do same things in JUnit \n  that&nbsp;I tend to stop discovering as soon as I have something working . \n  </font></span></div>\n  <div><span class=\"ygrps-yiv-20141139323270601-20122000\"><font size=\"2\"></font></span>&nbsp;</div>\n  <div><span class=\"ygrps-yiv-20141139323270601-20122000\"><font size=\"2\">This is certainly a more \n  elegant way of writing tests for Exception handling.</font></span></div>\n  <div><span class=\"ygrps-yiv-20141139323270601-20122000\"><font size=\"2\"></font></span>&nbsp;</div>\n  <div><span class=\"ygrps-yiv-20141139323270601-20122000\"><font size=\"2\">Cheers,</font></span></div>\n  <div><span class=\"ygrps-yiv-20141139323270601-20122000\"><font size=\"2\"></font></span>&nbsp;</div>\n  <div><span class=\"ygrps-yiv-20141139323270601-20122000\"><font size=\"2\">Sachin</font></span></div>\n  <div><span class=\"ygrps-yiv-20141139323270601-20122000\"><font size=\"2\"></font></span>&nbsp;</div>\n  <blockquote>\n    <div class=\"ygrps-yiv-20141139OutlookMessageHeader\" dir=\"ltr\" align=\"left\"><font face=\"Tahoma\"\n size=\"2\">-----Original Message-----<br><b>From:</b> Brian Button \n    [mailto:bbutton01@...]<br><b>Sent:</b> Tuesday, December 19, 2000 \n    9:08 PM<br><b>To:</b> junit@egroups.com<br><b>Subject:</b> RE: [junit] \n    Exception Handling Question<br><br></font></div>\n    <div><font size=\"2\"><span class=\"ygrps-yiv-20141139269200513-19122000\">I agree with what Sachin \n    said, with one minor change. There is another member function in Assert \n    called fail() which you can use:</span></font></div>\n    <div><font size=\"2\"><span class=\"ygrps-yiv-20141139269200513-19122000\"></span></font>&nbsp;</div>\n    <div><font size=\"2\"><span class=\"ygrps-yiv-20141139269200513-19122000\">public void testXXX( ) \n    throws Exception</span></font></div>\n    <div><font size=\"2\"><span class=\"ygrps-yiv-20141139269200513-19122000\">{</span></font></div>\n    <div><font size=\"2\"><span class=\"ygrps-yiv-20141139269200513-19122000\">&nbsp; \n    try</span></font></div>\n    <div><font size=\"2\"><span class=\"ygrps-yiv-20141139269200513-19122000\">&nbsp; \n{</span></font></div>\n    <div><font size=\"2\"><span class=\"ygrps-yiv-20141139269200513-19122000\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; \n    doMyStuffThatMightThrow( );</span></font></div>\n    <div><font size=\"2\"><span class=\"ygrps-yiv-20141139269200513-19122000\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; fail( \n    &quot;Didn&#39;t get my expected exception&quot; );</span></font></div>\n    <div><font size=\"2\"><span class=\"ygrps-yiv-20141139269200513-19122000\">&nbsp; \n}</span></font></div>\n    <div><font size=\"2\"><span class=\"ygrps-yiv-20141139269200513-19122000\">&nbsp; catch( \n    MyExpectedException e )</span></font></div>\n    <div><font size=\"2\"><span class=\"ygrps-yiv-20141139269200513-19122000\">&nbsp; \n{</span></font></div>\n    <div><font size=\"2\"><span class=\"ygrps-yiv-20141139269200513-19122000\">&nbsp; \n}</span></font></div>\n    <div><font size=\"2\"><span class=\"ygrps-yiv-20141139269200513-19122000\">}</span></font></div>\n    <div><font size=\"2\"></font>&nbsp;</div>\n    <div><font size=\"2\"><span class=\"ygrps-yiv-20141139269200513-19122000\">Same thing as the previous \n    poster, just replace his assert( false ) with fail().</span></font></div>\n    <div><font size=\"2\"><span class=\"ygrps-yiv-20141139269200513-19122000\"></span></font>&nbsp;</div>\n    <div><font size=\"2\"><span class=\"ygrps-yiv-20141139269200513-19122000\">bab</span></font></div>\n    <p><font size=\"2\">----<br>Brian Button&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; \n    bbutton@...<br>Senior Consultant&nbsp; Object Mentor, \n    Inc.</font> </p>\n    <blockquote\n style=\"PADDING-LEFT:5px;MARGIN-LEFT:5px;BORDER-LEFT:#000000 2px solid;\">\n      <div class=\"ygrps-yiv-20141139OutlookMessageHeader\" dir=\"ltr\" align=\"left\"><font face=\"Tahoma\"\n size=\"2\">-----Original Message-----<br><b>From:</b> sachin gupta \n      [mailto:sachin@...]<br><b>Sent:</b> Tuesday, December 19, 2000 \n      12:29 AM<br><b>To:</b> junit@egroups.com<br><b>Subject:</b> RE: [junit] \n      Exception Handling Question<br><br></font></div>\n      <div><span class=\"ygrps-yiv-20141139992582106-19122000\"><font size=\"2\">In case Exception is \n      mentioned in the throws clause of method you may try something like this \n      </font></span></div>\n      <div><span class=\"ygrps-yiv-20141139992582106-19122000\"><font\n size=\"2\"></font></span>&nbsp;</div>\n      <div><span class=\"ygrps-yiv-20141139992582106-19122000\"><font size=\"2\">try </font></span></div>\n      <div><span class=\"ygrps-yiv-20141139992582106-19122000\"><font size=\"2\">{</font></span></div>\n      <div><span class=\"ygrps-yiv-20141139992582106-19122000\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <font size=\"2\">method \n      with input that causes the expected Exception to be \n      thrown.</font></span></div>\n      <div><span class=\"ygrps-yiv-20141139992582106-19122000\"><font size=\"2\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; \n      assert(false);</font></span></div>\n      <div><span class=\"ygrps-yiv-20141139992582106-19122000\"><font size=\"2\">}</font></span></div>\n      <div><span class=\"ygrps-yiv-20141139992582106-19122000\"><font size=\"2\">catch (ExpectedException \n      e)</font></span></div>\n      <div><span class=\"ygrps-yiv-20141139992582106-19122000\"><font size=\"2\">{</font></span></div>\n      <div><span class=\"ygrps-yiv-20141139992582106-19122000\"><font\n size=\"2\">assert(true);</font></span></div>\n      <div><span class=\"ygrps-yiv-20141139992582106-19122000\"><font\n size=\"2\">}</font></span></div></blockquote><br><br><tt>To unsubscribe from \n    this group, send an email \n    to:<br>junit-unsubscribe@egroups.com<br><br></tt><br></blockquote><br><br><tt>To \n  unsubscribe from this group, send an email \n  to:<br>junit-unsubscribe@egroups.com<br><br></tt><br></blockquote></span></blockquote></html> \n</div>", 
